<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[227,348,925,951]" box="[227,348,925,951]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,348,925,951]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,348,925,951]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[226,1444,975,1115]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName authority="Wichard &amp; Espeland, 2022" authorityName="Wichard &amp; Espeland" authorityYear="2022" box="[227,500,975,1001]" class="Insecta" family="Dysoneuridae" genus="Cretapsyche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myanmari" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[227,500,975,1001]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Cretapsyche myanmari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[509,601,975,1001]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from all other species in the genus by having M branching before Rs in the forewing and an open thyridial cell. 
<taxonomicName authority="Wichard &amp; Espeland, 2022" authorityName="Wichard &amp; Espeland" authorityYear="2022" box="[966,1237,1012,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Dysoneuridae" genus="Cretapsyche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myanmari" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[966,1237,1012,1038]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Cretapsyche myanmari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1244,1334,1013,1039]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can also be distinguished in the male genitalia by the mesodorsal processes of tergum X, scale-shaped, each with two black spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
